1
00:00:05,538 --> 00:00:08,608
<i>Today, I bought a bank.</i>

2
00:00:11,711 --> 00:00:13,545
<i>From subscriptions,</i>

3
00:00:13,546 --> 00:00:15,381
<i>business software development,</i>

4
00:00:15,382 --> 00:00:18,218
<i>and the launch
of its Internet TV channel NEOXIS TV,</i>

5
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:21,153
<i>NEOXIS is the IT company
everyone's watching,</i>

6
00:00:21,154 --> 00:00:23,523
<i>and it just keeps growing.</i>

7
00:00:24,557 --> 00:00:27,427
<i>The company's founder,
President Kosei Neo,</i>

8
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:29,896
<i>operates under the philosophy
"For the People."</i>

9
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:32,264
<i>Just seven years
after founding the company,</i>

10
00:00:32,265 --> 00:00:34,934
<i>he built their HQ
in prime city real estate.</i>

11
00:00:36,503 --> 00:00:38,804
<i>And today,
the company officially finalized</i>

12
00:00:38,805 --> 00:00:41,841
<i>the acquisition of Vena Bank.</i>

13
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,744
<i>Having secured
a new foundation in finance,</i>

14
00:00:45,745 --> 00:00:47,881
<i>NEOXIS is entering a new phase</i>

15
00:00:49,149 --> 00:00:51,751
<i>and drawing enormous public attention--</i>

16
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,080
Let's go…

17
00:01:21,281 --> 00:01:22,115
Eito.

18
00:01:27,654 --> 00:01:28,488
Honey.

19
00:01:45,138 --> 00:01:48,708
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

20
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:52,945
<i>It's simply natural
that e-commerce and subscriptions</i>

21
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,413
<i>are killing off online and physical shops.</i>

22
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:55,314
A TRENDING PERSON
SECRETS OF SUCCESS FROM A BUSINESS LEADER

23
00:01:55,315 --> 00:01:57,483
<i>Business owners who lament that</i>

24
00:01:57,484 --> 00:01:58,383
SO RIGHT THAT I CAN’T ARGUE.
LOGICAL MONSTER!

25
00:01:58,384 --> 00:02:01,153
<i>are essentially admitting</i>

26
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:02,421
<i>they had never thought ahead.</i>

27
00:02:02,422 --> 00:02:06,525
<i>Someday,
robots and AI will displace workers,</i>

28
00:02:06,526 --> 00:02:08,193
<i>and they'll flood the streets.</i>

29
00:02:08,194 --> 00:02:11,297
<i>Failing to prepare for that is just naive.</i>

30
00:02:13,366 --> 00:02:15,367
Your statements

31
00:02:15,368 --> 00:02:18,770
always attract attention,
praised by some, condemned by others.

32
00:02:18,771 --> 00:02:20,672
Backlash

33
00:02:20,673 --> 00:02:21,740
TOGO FUND CEO
YOSHITAKA TOGO

34
00:02:21,741 --> 00:02:23,276
must be your favorite thing, huh?

35
00:02:24,110 --> 00:02:25,044
Yes.

36
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,714
The more I'm attacked,

37
00:02:28,348 --> 00:02:30,415
the more I'm reminded

38
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:32,819
of just how successful and envied I am.

39
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,221
It takes me back

40
00:02:36,523 --> 00:02:38,991
to when I first met you, Neo.

41
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,792
DISASTER VICTIM NETWORK

42
00:02:40,793 --> 00:02:43,496
<i>Through a crowdfunded welfare initiative
supporting disaster victims,</i>

43
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:46,431
- <i>you drew the world's attention…</i>
- Thank you.

44
00:02:46,432 --> 00:02:49,134
<i>…as a young philanthropist.</i>

45
00:02:49,135 --> 00:02:50,603
Thank you.

46
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:53,139
But I never missed

47
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:58,111
the whirlpool of ambition
lurking in your eyes.

48
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:00,413
You're a devil

49
00:03:01,214 --> 00:03:03,082
in the skin…

50
00:03:04,284 --> 00:03:05,118
of a humanitarian.

51
00:03:06,786 --> 00:03:10,757
My first impression of you
wasn't far off the mark, was it?

52
00:03:11,558 --> 00:03:14,627
My instinct to invest in you was right.

53
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:19,164
There was no Kosei Neo before Kosei Neo,

54
00:03:19,165 --> 00:03:21,166
and there will be

55
00:03:21,167 --> 00:03:22,902
no Kosei Neo after him.

56
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:27,140
The wild dream of dragging down Soman,

57
00:03:28,007 --> 00:03:31,978
the nation's top firm and replacing them…

58
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:35,113
I'm starting to think you might

59
00:03:35,114 --> 00:03:37,016
actually pull it off someday.

60
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,321
NEOXIS TOWER COMPLETION CEREMONY

61
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:44,790
In commemoration
of the NEOXIS Tower's completion,

62
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,726
we will now perform
the ribbon-cutting ceremony.

63
00:03:54,634 --> 00:03:56,802
Congratulations on the completion
of your own building.

64
00:03:56,803 --> 00:03:57,870
Thank you.

65
00:04:00,306 --> 00:04:02,175
If we launched
an acquisition bid against you,

66
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:04,209
you'd be done in seconds.

67
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:05,478
PRESIDENT OF SOMAN
HITOSHI ICHIMANDA

68
00:04:07,547 --> 00:04:09,181
When I built

69
00:04:09,182 --> 00:04:12,352
this building seven years ago,
that's exactly what I decided.

70
00:04:14,454 --> 00:04:16,422
This world is a game,

71
00:04:18,057 --> 00:04:19,058
and I was going

72
00:04:19,659 --> 00:04:21,394
to enjoy playing it
for as long as I could.

73
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:35,507
NEOXIS EXECUTIVE
TATSUKI TOMONO

74
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:38,877
Get in now on next year's
Tokyo Olympics partnership?

75
00:04:38,878 --> 00:04:41,113
Knock Soman out of the top spot

76
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:42,981
and put NEOXIS there instead?

77
00:04:42,982 --> 00:04:45,417
And on top of that, we're acquiring a bank

78
00:04:45,418 --> 00:04:46,853
only seven years after we were founded?

79
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,855
That's exactly why I promoted

80
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:51,624
all of you to the board.

81
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:54,894
Make it happen,

82
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:57,130
or quit.

83
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:01,066
Which sounds more fun? Choose.

84
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:02,969
NEOXIS SECRETARY
ERI NOMOTO

85
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:11,144
Now we're talking.
This is a fight worth having.

86
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:16,114
However, there are significant hurdles
before a final decision can be made.

87
00:05:16,115 --> 00:05:16,983
Tomono,

88
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:20,920
making that happen is your job.

89
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:23,956
Understood.

90
00:05:25,391 --> 00:05:26,892
If you push people too hard,

91
00:05:26,893 --> 00:05:28,461
they'll end up resenting you.

92
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:32,532
Maybe having a family
would mellow you out a little.

93
00:05:33,299 --> 00:05:34,534
A family, huh…

94
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:36,069
Nomoto…

95
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:41,174
I don't have good memories
when it comes to family.

96
00:05:41,741 --> 00:05:43,976
I'm sorry. I said something out of line.

97
00:05:46,579 --> 00:05:49,081
This is a gift from one of our clients.

98
00:05:49,082 --> 00:05:51,617
Eri, I think I've mentioned this before,

99
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:54,153
- but just throw that kind of thing away.
- Huh?

100
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:55,922
Throw it away?

101
00:05:56,522 --> 00:05:57,656
Look,

102
00:05:57,657 --> 00:05:58,890
I have no way of knowing

103
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:01,260
what anyone thinks of me
or what their motives are.

104
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:05,897
Then can I take it home?

105
00:06:05,898 --> 00:06:07,467
I've warned you.

106
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:10,168
If you’re okay with that, go ahead.

107
00:06:10,169 --> 00:06:11,571
Yes!

108
00:06:13,606 --> 00:06:14,841
Excuse me.

109
00:06:39,298 --> 00:06:41,299
After analyzing, we've concluded

110
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:44,337
that Vena Bank
is our only option for acquisition.

111
00:06:44,937 --> 00:06:46,606
A solid deal.

112
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:49,776
Impressive work, Takarabe.

113
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:53,011
I'd like to pat myself on the back

114
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:54,746
for poaching you from a megabank.

115
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:57,249
I hear Vena Holdings is open to the sale.

116
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,484
However…

117
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:01,587
However?

118
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:06,091
In addition to the sale price,

119
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:08,059
they're demanding
95,000 square meters of land

120
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:10,496
within the city.

121
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:13,932
With the Olympics just a year away,

122
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,634
land prices across the city are surging,

123
00:07:15,635 --> 00:07:18,403
making this
the worst possible time to look.

124
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:20,473
Don't make me say it again, Tomono.

125
00:07:22,341 --> 00:07:24,944
Making what I want happen…

126
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:26,979
that is what

127
00:07:28,147 --> 00:07:30,783
directly pays for all your lives.

128
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,421
Understood.

129
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:39,958
<i>The novel coronavirus upended</i>

130
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,360
<i>all of our lives.</i>

131
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:44,496
<i>Here's how things unfolded</i>

132
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:47,165
<i>leading up to the first-ever</i>

133
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:49,769
- <i>state of emergency declaration.</i>
- An unexpected enemy has appeared.

134
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,304
Due to the COVID-19 outbreak,

135
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:54,506
the Tokyo Olympics
have been postponed for a year,

136
00:07:54,507 --> 00:07:57,810
and all deals with partner companies
have been canceled.

137
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:00,780
All that remains are the debts.

138
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:03,348
As head of the financial division,

139
00:08:03,349 --> 00:08:04,716
I find this painful.

140
00:08:04,717 --> 00:08:06,852
<i>The unknown fear…</i>

141
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:09,588
The streets have emptied out.

142
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:11,089
<i>‎On March 11th…</i>

143
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:13,925
<i>- Due to COVID-19,</i>
- What is everyone doing, shut up at home?

144
00:08:13,926 --> 00:08:16,294
<i>the global economy…</i>

145
00:08:16,295 --> 00:08:18,597
<i>the spread of infection</i>

146
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:20,666
<i>declared it a pandemic…</i>

147
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:25,671
<i>‎In Tokyo, Prime Minister Abe…</i>

148
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,173
<i>‎A historical…</i>

149
00:08:28,774 --> 00:08:29,741
- <i>The country…</i>
- Sir?

150
00:08:29,742 --> 00:08:30,976
<i>…and local governments</i>

151
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:34,614
<i>have called the possibility of an outbreak
as 3 C's--</i>

152
00:08:35,781 --> 00:08:37,583
It's all right, Tomono.

153
00:08:39,051 --> 00:08:40,720
As expected of a founding member.

154
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,155
Sir…

155
00:08:44,924 --> 00:08:46,959
Starting today, your salary is doubled.

156
00:08:48,961 --> 00:08:51,898
Now is our chance!

157
00:08:54,901 --> 00:08:56,769
We're launching a new business.

158
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:44,316
We've doubled down
on subscription content,

159
00:09:44,317 --> 00:09:47,519
and we're rolling out online learning
and a new matching app.

160
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,588
Food delivery is performing well,

161
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:51,222
and our logistics are expanding.

162
00:09:51,223 --> 00:09:53,425
We have a pipeline with the MOH.

163
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:54,659
We're moving toward

164
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:57,296
entering the PCR testing
and vaccine distribution business.

165
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,564
If people won't come out,

166
00:09:59,565 --> 00:10:01,434
bring the business to them at home.

167
00:10:02,501 --> 00:10:05,471
Your foresight never ceases
to amaze me, sir.

168
00:10:08,674 --> 00:10:10,042
For the People.

169
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:12,712
I just thought

170
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:16,616
about what people actually need right now.

171
00:10:22,688 --> 00:10:24,656
<i>Following the death
of former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe,</i>

172
00:10:24,657 --> 00:10:27,460
<i>who was shot during a campaign speech,</i>

173
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:29,794
<i>condolences have poured in</i>

174
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:31,564
<i>from world leaders.</i>

175
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:34,265
<i>US President Biden</i>

176
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:36,102
<i>issued a statement on the 8th,</i>

177
00:10:36,669 --> 00:10:39,204
<i>saying, "I am shocked, outraged,</i>

178
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:40,206
<i>and deeply saddened."</i>

179
00:10:40,873 --> 00:10:43,709
Your regular checkup results
are all clear.

180
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:47,979
Heaven has granted you health

181
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:49,615
as yet another weapon, right?

182
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,254
We found the land for the acquisition.

183
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:58,323
Now we can negotiate with Vena Bank.

184
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,458
Where is the land?

185
00:10:59,959 --> 00:11:02,862
The Akari Housing Complex
and Akari Shopping Street in Arakawa Ward.

186
00:11:06,699 --> 00:11:08,334
The Akari Housing Complex

187
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:11,103
and Akari Shopping Street…

188
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:16,342
‎AKARI HOUSING COMPLEX
‎AKARI SHOPPING STREET

189
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:20,312
SHOPPING STREET

190
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:25,818
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

191
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:06,926
- This is everything.
- Thank you.

192
00:12:09,962 --> 00:12:12,131
Evictions at the Akari complex
are going smoothly.

193
00:12:12,631 --> 00:12:14,365
Due to the aging population,

194
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:16,168
80% of the units are already vacant.

195
00:12:22,374 --> 00:12:23,576
Thank you.

196
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:27,146
Thanks. Okay.

197
00:12:29,281 --> 00:12:30,382
Thank you.

198
00:12:31,117 --> 00:12:32,852
This is everything.

199
00:12:33,686 --> 00:12:34,520
Take care of it.

200
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,825
Tatsu from the record shop
just left the other day too.

201
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:42,327
Can't be helped.

202
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:44,997
The days when a bookshop
could make a living are over.

203
00:12:45,531 --> 00:12:46,531
Kinpei,

204
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:49,068
you should shut down
that print shop while you still can.

205
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:51,503
What are you saying?

206
00:12:51,504 --> 00:12:52,738
I won't let the times beat me.

207
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:56,208
Chairman…

208
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:58,277
No…

209
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:00,111
- No…
- Hey!

210
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:01,713
- Thank you for everything.
- It's okay.

211
00:13:01,714 --> 00:13:02,948
- Hayashi, take care.
- Yes.

212
00:13:04,049 --> 00:13:05,151
Call us, okay?

213
00:13:05,651 --> 00:13:06,684
- Take care.
- See you.

214
00:13:06,685 --> 00:13:08,286
- Take care.
- Be careful.

215
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:09,455
- Take care.
- Stay cheerful.

216
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:12,892
- See you.
- Take care.

217
00:13:17,363 --> 00:13:20,231
70% of Akari Shopping Street
has been vacated.

218
00:13:20,232 --> 00:13:22,100
The shops and factories that remain

219
00:13:22,101 --> 00:13:24,403
are on their last legs
due to the recession and COVID.

220
00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:28,573
We will proceed carefully,

221
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:31,210
with the understanding of the community.

222
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:38,449
Please understand that this proposal

223
00:13:38,450 --> 00:13:40,219
is for the future
of Akari Shopping Street.

224
00:13:42,855 --> 00:13:45,624
NEOXIS is a company
that works for the people.

225
00:13:46,292 --> 00:13:47,425
We have examined this

226
00:13:47,426 --> 00:13:49,527
from every angle to ensure

227
00:13:49,528 --> 00:13:51,931
you can continue living here
with peace of mind.

228
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:54,700
He really has it together.

229
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:58,303
We will also help with housing

230
00:13:58,304 --> 00:14:00,171
and new business locations

231
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:01,841
after you leave the street.

232
00:14:02,374 --> 00:14:05,677
We will provide dedicated support

233
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:09,281
to guide
your future business ventures as well.

234
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:13,752
NEOXIS will be with you
every step of the way.

235
00:14:14,553 --> 00:14:16,588
I wouldn't mind being taken care of

236
00:14:16,589 --> 00:14:17,789
by this young man.

237
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:18,790
- How about it?
- Hideko!

238
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:20,458
Give me a break!

239
00:14:20,459 --> 00:14:23,194
I'm not falling for that kind of talk!

240
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:25,163
- Me too!
- Yeah!

241
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:27,665
- You're just causing trouble…
- Yeah!

242
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:31,269
- Go home!
- Yeah!

243
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,404
Go home!

244
00:14:33,606 --> 00:14:36,008
<i>It's fine. I'm used to this sort of thing.</i>

245
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:39,377
That's Tsuchiya for you,
trained at a major firm.

246
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:42,814
The people here are probably
holding out for a higher payout.

247
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:45,417
Feel free to spend the money.
We want to move quickly.

248
00:14:48,587 --> 00:14:51,924
That concludes the explanation
of the compensation amount for vacating.

249
00:14:52,691 --> 00:14:54,827
I believe this is more than sufficient.

250
00:14:59,198 --> 00:15:00,199
Hey!

251
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:04,135
<i>If you think it will go your way,
that's a mistake!</i>

252
00:15:04,136 --> 00:15:06,805
- <i>Yeah! There's no way we're leaving!</i>
- <i>Yeah!</i>

253
00:15:07,873 --> 00:15:09,074
Double the payout.

254
00:15:09,775 --> 00:15:11,976
Then how about double the payout?

255
00:15:11,977 --> 00:15:12,978
What?

256
00:15:13,679 --> 00:15:15,280
I hope you can see

257
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:16,648
what a favorable deal this is.

258
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:18,817
Don't mess with us! Dammit!

259
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:23,121
Say something!

260
00:15:23,122 --> 00:15:24,957
- This is going nowhere.
- Yeah!

261
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,828
Chairman, say something!

262
00:15:30,863 --> 00:15:33,966
This is our hometown.

263
00:15:35,834 --> 00:15:37,535
Selling our hometown for money…

264
00:15:37,536 --> 00:15:38,604
Five times.

265
00:15:39,171 --> 00:15:40,039
Then…

266
00:15:40,973 --> 00:15:42,173
how about five times the amount?

267
00:15:42,174 --> 00:15:43,475
Huh? Five times?

268
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,411
- Huh? Wait…
- Oh…

269
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:48,846
- So how much would five times come to?
- Hideko!

270
00:15:48,847 --> 00:15:50,949
- Hide, stop! Go back!
- He said five times!

271
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,818
- <i>Shut up! Go back!</i>
- <i>If it's five times…</i>

272
00:15:53,819 --> 00:15:56,555
What an unassuming chairman.

273
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,692
He's just a gentle soul.

274
00:16:00,826 --> 00:16:01,894
We…

275
00:16:03,062 --> 00:16:05,998
will not sell our hometown for money.

276
00:16:07,499 --> 00:16:08,232
<i>You got it!</i>

277
00:16:08,233 --> 00:16:10,202
- Watch Tomono.
- <i>Go home!</i>

278
00:16:10,736 --> 00:16:11,971
Based on the circumstances,

279
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:14,306
people can change in any number of ways.

280
00:16:14,907 --> 00:16:17,543
But that way of going about things…

281
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:21,179
Taking their hometown from them…

282
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:22,314
"For the People."

283
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:25,484
I'm…

284
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:29,388
going to give these people
the money they'll need going forward.

285
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:36,261
Push for five times.

286
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:46,170
- From their own pockets?
- Hey! Isn't that right?

287
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:48,539
- That's too much!
- That's okay!

288
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:50,508
- Is it okay for him to drink this much?
- It's okay.

289
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:51,943
- See?
- Oh…

290
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:53,344
- Come on!
- Hey!

291
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:54,912
- Hey, listen!
- Yeah…

292
00:16:54,913 --> 00:16:57,816
What's this
about halting our print orders?

293
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:00,285
Just the other day,

294
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:02,888
our flyer printing orders

295
00:17:03,455 --> 00:17:05,557
suddenly dried up too.

296
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:09,194
Meat and vegetables
aren't coming in at all either.

297
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:12,397
That's got to be those guys' doing.

298
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:15,967
- Hey!
- Oh, I'll take him home.

299
00:17:15,968 --> 00:17:17,235
- I'm fine!
- Let's go!

300
00:17:17,236 --> 00:17:18,503
- Hey!
- Be careful.

301
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:20,304
- From now on…
- Let's go.

302
00:17:20,305 --> 00:17:22,273
Our future is still…

303
00:17:22,274 --> 00:17:23,307
- Oh, no!
- Oh!

304
00:17:23,308 --> 00:17:25,676
Watch out!

305
00:17:25,677 --> 00:17:27,245
- Hey!
- Oh, no!

306
00:17:27,246 --> 00:17:28,413
- Hey!
- You okay?

307
00:17:28,414 --> 00:17:30,281
- You drank too much!
- Hey!

308
00:17:30,282 --> 00:17:31,382
- Let's go!
- I'm okay!

309
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:32,884
Hang in there, Kinpei!

310
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,919
What do you mean by "Hang in there"?

311
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,821
- How am I supposed to hang in there?
- Okay.

312
00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:39,157
- Sorry, sorry.
- Okay…

313
00:17:39,158 --> 00:17:40,291
- We're okay.
- Okay?

314
00:17:40,292 --> 00:17:41,793
- We're going home.
- How am I…

315
00:17:41,794 --> 00:17:42,927
- They're about at their limit.
- I'm okay, you know!

316
00:17:42,928 --> 00:17:43,896
No worries.

317
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:46,998
MUROTA BUTCHER SHOP

318
00:17:46,999 --> 00:17:48,634
Sorry for the wait.

319
00:17:49,435 --> 00:17:51,102
Kinpei has another hangover?

320
00:17:51,103 --> 00:17:52,204
Yeah…

321
00:17:52,938 --> 00:17:54,439
- Thanks, see you.
- Thank you.

322
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,541
Okay.

323
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:01,080
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

324
00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:21,533
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

325
00:18:50,229 --> 00:18:53,665
FUNERAL

326
00:19:05,177 --> 00:19:08,147
‎-Who is that?
‎-That's the president of NEOXIS.

327
00:19:09,381 --> 00:19:11,917
‎He looks exactly like Eito.

328
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:24,929
KOSEI NEO

329
00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:26,131
My deepest condolences.

330
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:32,137
So you're the president?

331
00:19:33,372 --> 00:19:35,274
You people killed Kinpei.

332
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:37,009
Say something!

333
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:54,026
My sincerest condolences.

334
00:20:30,796 --> 00:20:32,097
Excuse me.

335
00:20:40,939 --> 00:20:43,442
As our philosophy, "For the People,"

336
00:20:44,676 --> 00:20:46,644
is what we're doing now

337
00:20:46,645 --> 00:20:48,780
truly for the people?

338
00:20:52,217 --> 00:20:54,218
Shouldn't we return to the ideals

339
00:20:54,219 --> 00:20:56,420
we had when we started
the welfare business?

340
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:59,558
We built social trust
through our welfare business.

341
00:21:00,859 --> 00:21:03,895
We've moved
into a completely different stage now.

342
00:21:07,065 --> 00:21:10,402
The welfare work was just
a means to gain that trust?

343
00:21:15,274 --> 00:21:17,676
Just as the people
of Akari Shopping Street said…

344
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:20,912
We killed that man!

345
00:21:30,222 --> 00:21:31,122
RESIGNATION LETTER

346
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:33,525
This is Tomono's letter of resignation.

347
00:21:37,195 --> 00:21:39,164
I see.

348
00:21:43,902 --> 00:21:45,036
Tomono's parents

349
00:21:45,037 --> 00:21:47,673
have been ill,
so things must be rough for him.

350
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:54,112
As severance pay,
maybe around 100 million yen?

351
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,481
Could you arrange that for him?

352
00:21:57,249 --> 00:21:59,785
I'm sorry. Please ask someone else.

353
00:22:02,354 --> 00:22:05,190
Today is also my last day.

354
00:22:07,025 --> 00:22:07,859
You too?

355
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:10,629
Thank you for everything.

356
00:22:11,763 --> 00:22:12,764
Eri…

357
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,300
How much do you want?

358
00:22:16,535 --> 00:22:17,736
Ten billion yen.

359
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:17,963
Sir.

360
00:23:22,868 --> 00:23:25,470
I heard a disturbing rumor,
so I thought I should tell you.

361
00:23:29,641 --> 00:23:31,443
I can't believe this!

362
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:34,713
That's an outrageous sum.

363
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,648
I can't believe Vena Bank

364
00:23:37,649 --> 00:23:39,484
had such enormous hidden liabilities.

365
00:23:40,218 --> 00:23:41,786
As the person in charge,

366
00:23:41,787 --> 00:23:43,155
I'm sorry for not catching this.

367
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:48,693
Takarabe, don't expect
a severance package.

368
00:23:50,328 --> 00:23:51,930
Are you dismissing me?

369
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:55,000
I'm sorry.

370
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:58,470
This is my fault
for failing to see through you.

371
00:23:59,037 --> 00:24:00,906
I am truly sorry.

372
00:24:10,882 --> 00:24:12,184
What are we going to do, sir?

373
00:24:12,684 --> 00:24:15,953
This debt is enough
to threaten the company's survival.

374
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,456
It'll be fine.

375
00:24:18,723 --> 00:24:20,225
Do you understand the situation?

376
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:22,259
We're losing…

377
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,729
the public's trust
as well as everything else.

378
00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:30,602
We're…

379
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:34,104
covered in graffiti and called murderers.

380
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:36,340
Can't you see that as a badge of honor

381
00:24:36,341 --> 00:24:38,844
for everything we've accomplished?

382
00:24:44,182 --> 00:24:45,217
I can't…

383
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:47,686
follow you anymore.

384
00:24:50,789 --> 00:24:51,756
That's a shame.

385
00:24:57,662 --> 00:24:58,864
Thank you for everything.

386
00:25:01,233 --> 00:25:02,733
AN IT FIRM THAT HAS HAD A SUICIDE VICTIM

387
00:25:02,734 --> 00:25:04,235
TRAITOR

388
00:25:04,236 --> 00:25:06,171
CORPORATE PRESSURE THAT DESTROYED
THE SHOPPING STREET

389
00:25:11,576 --> 00:25:13,845
WEEKLY TABLOID

390
00:25:23,221 --> 00:25:26,358
Quite a strong headwind blowing, it seems.

391
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:30,361
A strong headwind
means you can fly higher.

392
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,197
But I thought it would be good

393
00:25:32,998 --> 00:25:35,567
to ask for some help this time.

394
00:25:36,701 --> 00:25:38,670
I've brought in a partner
who's right for you.

395
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,341
A partner?

396
00:25:54,286 --> 00:25:56,922
Long time no see.
I'm Ichimanda from Soman.

397
00:25:57,689 --> 00:25:58,957
The president of Soman.

398
00:25:59,524 --> 00:26:01,059
If we launched
an acquisition bid against you,

399
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,928
you'd be done in seconds.

400
00:26:05,430 --> 00:26:07,265
Togo filled me in.

401
00:26:08,033 --> 00:26:09,166
You're not saying

402
00:26:09,167 --> 00:26:12,303
we'd let Soman swallow us up?

403
00:26:12,304 --> 00:26:15,006
That's one option on the table.

404
00:26:20,812 --> 00:26:22,046
You're not saying

405
00:26:22,047 --> 00:26:25,149
we'd let Soman swallow us up?

406
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:27,852
That's one option on the table.

407
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,827
Have we really caused you
that much concern?

408
00:26:36,528 --> 00:26:38,963
If you insist,

409
00:26:38,964 --> 00:26:40,397
as the top company,

410
00:26:40,398 --> 00:26:43,668
we can certainly throw a lifeline
to a struggling peer.

411
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:48,072
As Togo is the one asking,

412
00:26:48,073 --> 00:26:50,041
I can hardly say no.

413
00:27:02,387 --> 00:27:03,788
Would it be all right if I declined?

414
00:27:04,889 --> 00:27:05,757
Sure.

415
00:27:07,325 --> 00:27:08,860
You're something else, Neo.

416
00:27:10,161 --> 00:27:13,264
Still running full speed
on a sinking ship.

417
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:15,367
But I just can't bear

418
00:27:16,167 --> 00:27:18,703
to watch your ship go under.

419
00:27:20,372 --> 00:27:22,907
You've completely misread the situation,
Togo.

420
00:27:25,877 --> 00:27:26,845
Ichimanda.

421
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:29,813
Regarding the generative AI leader
Spread AI,

422
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:32,316
which you've been courting,

423
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:34,852
robotic and AI development
will now proceed jointly

424
00:27:34,853 --> 00:27:37,689
with our company.

425
00:27:38,356 --> 00:27:39,423
We finalized

426
00:27:39,424 --> 00:27:42,060
that contract today.

427
00:27:43,194 --> 00:27:44,094
No way.

428
00:27:44,095 --> 00:27:48,366
That gives us a foothold
for fundraising, doesn't it, Togo?

429
00:27:49,534 --> 00:27:51,236
When did you manage to…

430
00:27:53,271 --> 00:27:55,607
Wouldn't you have been better off
getting on board our ship?

431
00:27:57,409 --> 00:27:58,576
If you'd like,

432
00:27:59,711 --> 00:28:00,545
I'll have a seat

433
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:02,247
ready for you.

434
00:28:03,782 --> 00:28:04,649
Ichimanda,

435
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:07,819
thank you for making the trip.

436
00:28:08,887 --> 00:28:09,821
Excuse me.

437
00:28:26,638 --> 00:28:29,708
FALLEN CHARISMATIC STAR KOSEI NEO SIGNS…

438
00:28:34,846 --> 00:28:37,916
A DEVELOPMENT CONTRACT WITH SPREAD AI
FOR A MIRACULOUS COMEBACK

439
00:29:07,979 --> 00:29:09,379
I'm excited.

440
00:29:09,380 --> 00:29:10,380
- RUTHLESS, MERCILESS, MURDEROUS CEO
- JUSTICE!

441
00:29:10,381 --> 00:29:12,450
<i>Huh? About what?</i>

442
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:15,720
I have a feeling a new stage is beginning.

443
00:29:16,354 --> 00:29:17,789
I don't think I'll be able to sleep.

444
00:29:19,491 --> 00:29:22,427
<i>Shouldn't you look back at yourself
before all that?</i>

445
00:29:23,194 --> 00:29:24,729
Look back at myself? Me?

446
00:29:25,864 --> 00:29:27,097
<i>You've risen</i>

447
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:29,299
<i>by exploiting people's misfortune</i>

448
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:31,935
<i>and have built on people's sacrifices.</i>

449
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:33,671
<i>That's my analysis.</i>

450
00:29:36,574 --> 00:29:37,742
Amazing.

451
00:29:38,343 --> 00:29:39,944
That's a sharp observation.

452
00:29:40,678 --> 00:29:41,946
<i>Thank you.</i>

453
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:46,351
But I think you're overlooking one thing.

454
00:29:48,353 --> 00:29:50,521
Even if there are small sacrifices,

455
00:29:50,522 --> 00:29:54,759
my actions may save far more people.

456
00:29:55,727 --> 00:29:57,028
<i>You're lonely, aren't you?</i>

457
00:29:57,595 --> 00:29:59,596
No, I'm not.

458
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:01,099
Because I have you.

459
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:49,681
The future, huh?

460
00:31:04,329 --> 00:31:06,463
<i>Just seven years
after founding the company,</i>

461
00:31:06,464 --> 00:31:07,698
<i>he built their HQ
in prime city real estate.</i>

462
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:09,266
<i>You're a devil in the skin…</i>

463
00:31:09,267 --> 00:31:10,468
<i>of a humanitarian.</i>

464
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:16,006
<i>Now is our chance!</i>

465
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:16,773
NEOXIS TOWER COMPLETION CEREMONY

466
00:31:16,774 --> 00:31:20,344
<i>If we launched an acquisition bid
against you, you'd be done in seconds.</i>

467
00:31:20,345 --> 00:31:22,413
<i>You've completely misread
the situation, Togo.</i>

468
00:31:24,482 --> 00:31:26,984
<i>I promoted all of you to the board.
Make it happen,</i>

469
00:31:26,985 --> 00:31:28,385
<i>or quit.</i>

470
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:29,553
<i>Which sounds more fun?</i>

471
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:31,922
<i>Making what I want happen…</i>

472
00:31:31,923 --> 00:31:35,593
<i>that is what directly pays for your lives.</i>

473
00:31:38,129 --> 00:31:39,696
<i>We've concluded that Vena Bank</i>

474
00:31:39,697 --> 00:31:42,099
- <i>is our only option for acquisition.</i>
- <i>…had such enormous hidden liabilities.</i>

475
00:31:42,100 --> 00:31:45,469
<i>This is my fault
for failing to see through you.</i>

476
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:48,172
<i>Today is also my last day.</i>

477
00:31:50,775 --> 00:31:53,110
<i>If you think it will go your way,
that's a mistake!</i>

478
00:31:53,111 --> 00:31:54,979
<i>We killed that man!</i>

479
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:06,357
<i>You're lonely, aren't you?</i>

480
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:42,659
LOW HEART RATE

481
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:44,896
WARNING

482
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:54,165
<i>Am I…</i>

483
00:33:55,433 --> 00:33:56,567
<i>alive?</i>

484
00:34:05,176 --> 00:34:06,177
<i>Where…</i>

485
00:34:07,345 --> 00:34:08,379
<i>am I?</i>

486
00:34:12,350 --> 00:34:14,218
It's a miracle.

487
00:34:15,119 --> 00:34:18,022
To be resuscitated after a cardiac arrest…

488
00:34:18,990 --> 00:34:20,324
Please call my doctor.

489
00:34:20,992 --> 00:34:23,728
Dr. Nishihara at Seiko-dai Hospital.

490
00:34:24,662 --> 00:34:25,762
Huh?

491
00:34:25,763 --> 00:34:27,498
Please call him immediately.

492
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:29,800
Remarkably,

493
00:34:29,801 --> 00:34:31,668
there are no abnormalities

494
00:34:31,669 --> 00:34:33,771
in the bones, brain, or internal organs.

495
00:34:34,505 --> 00:34:36,607
You're fit for immediate discharge.

496
00:34:38,810 --> 00:34:39,844
Yes.

497
00:34:42,180 --> 00:34:43,314
Then, I'll leave…

498
00:34:43,815 --> 00:34:45,015
Please.

499
00:34:45,016 --> 00:34:48,352
- You really should wait a bit--
- Are my clothes here?

500
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:53,991
Here you go.

501
00:34:59,964 --> 00:35:00,798
These…

502
00:35:01,833 --> 00:35:03,201
aren't my clothes.

503
00:35:03,801 --> 00:35:04,702
Or my wallet.

504
00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:08,171
But you were brought in wearing these.

505
00:35:08,172 --> 00:35:09,407
There's no mistake.

506
00:35:33,931 --> 00:35:34,765
To NEOXIS.

507
00:35:35,399 --> 00:35:37,034
NEOXIS?

508
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:39,437
Do you know NEOXIS?

509
00:35:40,004 --> 00:35:41,304
I'm sorry, I don't.

510
00:35:41,305 --> 00:35:43,975
- Then I'll tell you the address.
- Please.

511
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:48,246
TAXI

512
00:36:08,399 --> 00:36:10,234
My company's building is gone.

513
00:36:17,808 --> 00:36:19,076
The whole building is gone.

514
00:36:22,346 --> 00:36:23,447
What's going on?

515
00:36:25,216 --> 00:36:26,817
Sir, please pay.

516
00:36:36,494 --> 00:36:37,795
Tap to pay, please.

517
00:36:38,696 --> 00:36:39,564
Tap?

518
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:41,065
Tap to pay.

519
00:36:42,166 --> 00:36:46,103
Wait. Am I worth that much to be touched?

520
00:36:47,038 --> 00:36:49,040
Huh? What?

521
00:37:11,095 --> 00:37:12,863
Why can I see this well?

522
00:37:24,342 --> 00:37:25,676
I look young.

523
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:35,886
Birthmark…

524
00:37:37,888 --> 00:37:39,156
I don't have my birthmark…

525
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:44,929
Is this…

526
00:37:49,934 --> 00:37:51,168
me?

527
00:37:54,872 --> 00:37:55,873
No…

528
00:38:23,034 --> 00:38:25,902
"Shinzo Abe returns
to the position of prime minister

529
00:38:25,903 --> 00:38:27,138
for a second term."

530
00:38:30,207 --> 00:38:31,809
Abe should be dead.

531
00:38:36,447 --> 00:38:38,115
"December 27th…

532
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:41,152
2012."

533
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:48,559
"2012."

534
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:51,362
"End of the year weather report"?

535
00:38:55,299 --> 00:39:00,905
‎2012 END OF THE YEAR
‎WEATHER FORECAST

536
00:39:02,907 --> 00:39:03,808
No way.

537
00:39:11,849 --> 00:39:13,584
AKB at the height of their popularity.

538
00:39:15,486 --> 00:39:17,088
It's 2012.

539
00:39:22,993 --> 00:39:24,028
Time travel?

540
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:53,791
At that time…

541
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:56,227
Someone…

542
00:39:57,695 --> 00:39:58,629
Eito.

543
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:03,033
Are you all right, Eito?

544
00:40:05,403 --> 00:40:06,237
Eito?

545
00:40:07,171 --> 00:40:08,105
I was looking for you.

546
00:40:10,207 --> 00:40:11,142
You are…

547
00:40:13,878 --> 00:40:15,780
Have you forgotten your father?

548
00:40:17,381 --> 00:40:18,482
Father?

549
00:40:28,726 --> 00:40:30,027
You're all right.

550
00:40:30,761 --> 00:40:32,663
- Thank goodness.
- Eito.

551
00:40:33,364 --> 00:40:35,332
- Let's go home.
- Huh?

552
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:36,901
Are you all right?

553
00:40:38,035 --> 00:40:39,603
I'll take you. Don't worry.

554
00:40:40,304 --> 00:40:42,573
I'll take you home.

555
00:40:48,179 --> 00:40:50,714
<i>I still don't understand.</i>

556
00:40:52,583 --> 00:40:56,120
<i>Is this truly the world of 2012?</i>

557
00:40:59,890 --> 00:41:03,461
<i>But something feels different
from time travel.</i>

558
00:41:06,096 --> 00:41:06,931
<i>Because I…</i>

559
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:09,800
<i>The current me is being recognized</i>

560
00:41:10,434 --> 00:41:12,303
<i>as this man's son, Eito.</i>

561
00:41:16,707 --> 00:41:19,343
<i>Like a reincarnation from an anime?</i>

562
00:41:20,778 --> 00:41:21,612
<i>No…</i>

563
00:41:22,847 --> 00:41:24,114
<i>So then the current me</i>

564
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:26,217
<i>is no longer Kosei Neo?</i>

565
00:41:34,558 --> 00:41:35,459
<i>This is…</i>

566
00:41:36,627 --> 00:41:38,863
<i>Akari Shopping Street, the place I forced</i>

567
00:41:39,597 --> 00:41:40,865
<i>residents to vacate.</i>

568
00:41:43,634 --> 00:41:44,568
<i>I remember now.</i>

569
00:41:45,369 --> 00:41:46,403
<i>This man is…</i>

570
00:41:47,071 --> 00:41:48,072
We…

571
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,174
won't sell our hometown

572
00:41:50,941 --> 00:41:52,142
for money.

573
00:41:52,743 --> 00:41:54,144
The unassuming chairman

574
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:56,714
of Akari Shopping Street.

575
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:13,964
‎NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

576
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:19,103
We're here.

577
00:42:24,375 --> 00:42:26,309
Hey!

578
00:42:26,310 --> 00:42:28,912
- Be quiet.
- We're playing shogi.

579
00:42:28,913 --> 00:42:32,181
- Hey!
- Oh!

580
00:42:32,182 --> 00:42:34,952
- You okay?
- The house will start falling apart…

581
00:42:36,820 --> 00:42:38,054
You okay?

582
00:42:38,055 --> 00:42:40,523
- No way! Here he is!
- Then…

583
00:42:40,524 --> 00:42:43,860
- Here he is!
- Eito!

584
00:42:43,861 --> 00:42:45,128
- Eito!
- Hey!

585
00:42:45,129 --> 00:42:47,297
- Welcome back!
- Hey!

586
00:42:47,298 --> 00:42:49,699
- Hey!
- I'm so glad!

587
00:42:49,700 --> 00:42:52,101
- Hey!
- Yeah!

588
00:42:52,102 --> 00:42:53,003
I'm glad!

589
00:42:53,604 --> 00:42:55,506
Eito! Congrats!

590
00:42:56,807 --> 00:42:57,941
<i>This man</i>

591
00:42:57,942 --> 00:43:00,276
<i>is the printing factory owner</i>

592
00:43:00,277 --> 00:43:03,047
<i>who was driven to his end
and then took his own life.</i>

593
00:43:03,781 --> 00:43:05,416
Eito!

594
00:43:06,150 --> 00:43:07,083
<i>The men who were openly hostile to me</i>

595
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:09,886
- <i>at the funeral.</i>
- You came back!

596
00:43:09,887 --> 00:43:10,787
Long time no see!

597
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:12,121
Eito!

598
00:43:12,122 --> 00:43:14,557
Hey! Stop it!

599
00:43:14,558 --> 00:43:15,525
Come here!

600
00:43:15,526 --> 00:43:17,393
- Sit here!
- Here!

601
00:43:17,394 --> 00:43:19,796
- Come here!
- Sit here!

602
00:43:19,797 --> 00:43:20,763
Bring him a cup!

603
00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:23,566
Everyone, listen up.

604
00:43:23,567 --> 00:43:24,601
Listen up.

605
00:43:24,602 --> 00:43:26,603
- Yes.
- Today…

606
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:28,638
Today, we raise a glass to Eito!

607
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:31,074
Right, Eito? Congrats on your discharge!

608
00:43:31,075 --> 00:43:34,544
Cheers!

609
00:43:34,545 --> 00:43:36,913
Hey!

610
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:40,084
He made it.

611
00:43:40,684 --> 00:43:41,952
Cheers!

612
00:43:42,486 --> 00:43:44,787
Welcome back!

613
00:43:44,788 --> 00:43:47,924
Eito. By the way…

614
00:43:47,925 --> 00:43:49,459
Do you remember the accident?

615
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:50,526
Accident?

616
00:43:50,527 --> 00:43:54,263
His memory's a bit hazy.

617
00:43:54,264 --> 00:43:56,633
He was at death's door.

618
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:58,569
Of course he can't remember.
It's only natural.

619
00:43:59,269 --> 00:44:00,237
I'm sorry about that.

620
00:44:01,105 --> 00:44:03,841
I can't believe something that heavy
fell on your head.

621
00:44:05,442 --> 00:44:06,443
Okay.

622
00:44:09,380 --> 00:44:10,480
Sarasa,

623
00:44:10,481 --> 00:44:13,316
Dad brought some sweet potato chips.
Let's eat them together.

624
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:15,718
Sure. Thanks. Just leave them there.

625
00:44:15,719 --> 00:44:18,088
These are so good.
Oh, I'll make some tea now.

626
00:44:31,735 --> 00:44:34,138
Eito! Eito!

627
00:44:35,105 --> 00:44:38,709
<i>You lost consciousness protecting Sarasa.</i>

628
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:41,378
Protecting Sarasa?

629
00:44:42,913 --> 00:44:45,181
You came back from cardiac arrest.

630
00:44:45,182 --> 00:44:47,917
The heavens were watching over him.

631
00:44:47,918 --> 00:44:49,886
You're such a good boy,

632
00:44:49,887 --> 00:44:52,356
the heavens kept you alive.

633
00:44:54,291 --> 00:44:57,493
- Eito!
- Kayo!

634
00:44:57,494 --> 00:44:58,861
Let's have today's oden together.

635
00:44:58,862 --> 00:45:00,029
Let's party!

636
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:01,064
No!

637
00:45:01,065 --> 00:45:04,033
No, he just got back from the hospital.

638
00:45:04,034 --> 00:45:05,902
- He can't…
- What are you saying?

639
00:45:05,903 --> 00:45:07,370
- Eito. Hey!
- Drinking…

640
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:10,641
- Some oden?
- Want some oden?

641
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:20,349
You've had a long day.

642
00:45:20,350 --> 00:45:21,785
Go rest in your room.

643
00:45:22,419 --> 00:45:23,253
Here, your phone.

644
00:45:39,903 --> 00:45:41,472
<i>This is Eito's room.</i>

645
00:45:59,890 --> 00:46:00,891
<i>He looks like me.</i>

646
00:46:11,135 --> 00:46:12,336
<i>Eito Nomoto.</i>

647
00:46:12,870 --> 00:46:16,073
<i>Born June 1st, 1982.</i>

648
00:46:17,641 --> 00:46:18,475
<i>So in 2012,</i>

649
00:46:19,209 --> 00:46:21,979
<i>Eito is…</i>

650
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,014
<i>30 years old.</i>

651
00:46:25,816 --> 00:46:27,417
<i>What kind of person is he?</i>

652
00:46:37,027 --> 00:46:39,329
<i>It seems Eito graduated
from a national university</i>

653
00:46:39,963 --> 00:46:42,899
<i>and had a job lined up at a major company,</i>

654
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:46,637
<i>but when his mother suddenly died
while his father was battling cancer,</i>

655
00:46:47,538 --> 00:46:49,640
<i>he took over this dry cleaning shop</i>

656
00:46:50,340 --> 00:46:52,942
<i>and worked to revitalize
the shopping street</i>

657
00:46:52,943 --> 00:46:55,045
<i>alongside his father after he recovered.</i>

658
00:46:56,213 --> 00:46:58,749
<i>He gives his all for those in need</i>

659
00:46:59,850 --> 00:47:01,785
<i>and hates dishonesty.</i>

660
00:47:02,753 --> 00:47:06,857
<i>A man who has lived an honest life…
The exact…</i>

661
00:47:07,691 --> 00:47:09,626
<i>opposite of me…</i>

662
00:47:12,996 --> 00:47:14,464
Can I come in?

663
00:47:24,741 --> 00:47:26,009
<i>This person…</i>

664
00:47:27,211 --> 00:47:28,812
<i>I saw her at the funeral.</i>

665
00:47:36,553 --> 00:47:37,387
No…

666
00:47:41,692 --> 00:47:43,293
Thanks for saving me.

667
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:47,598
<i>Could this be…</i>

668
00:47:48,565 --> 00:47:49,666
<i>the Sarasa…</i>

669
00:47:50,801 --> 00:47:53,502
<i>that Eito risked his life</i>

670
00:47:53,503 --> 00:47:54,938
<i>to protect?</i>

671
00:47:56,206 --> 00:47:59,476
I'm so glad you're alive.

672
00:48:03,313 --> 00:48:04,414
Yeah…

673
00:48:07,718 --> 00:48:09,353
I just came to say that.

674
00:48:11,655 --> 00:48:14,391
<i>She's like a completely different person.</i>

675
00:48:17,027 --> 00:48:18,028
Well then…

676
00:48:32,943 --> 00:48:34,577
<i>And Eito Nomoto,</i>

677
00:48:34,578 --> 00:48:37,848
<i>who looks exactly like me, Kosei Neo,</i>

678
00:48:38,348 --> 00:48:41,651
<i>tried to save her
and died from the accident</i>

679
00:48:41,652 --> 00:48:44,821
<i>and I was reborn into his body…</i>

680
00:48:49,626 --> 00:48:50,527
But why?

681
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:51,761
NEXT EPISODE
I CAN'T RETURN TO MY FORMER BODY?

682
00:48:51,762 --> 00:48:52,795
<i>How can I go back?</i>

683
00:48:52,796 --> 00:48:55,932
<i>Do I have to continue
living as Eito Nomoto?</i>

684
00:48:55,933 --> 00:48:58,067
What is this? This is delicious!

685
00:48:58,068 --> 00:49:01,304
<i>I want to make this a hit and bring life
back to the shopping street!</i>

686
00:49:01,305 --> 00:49:03,572
Eito is doing his best.

687
00:49:03,573 --> 00:49:06,142
Now that I’ve decided,
I’m going to definitely make it happen!

688
00:49:06,143 --> 00:49:07,077
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
